lace (r=\r\nealized Self) may first construct the palace over time and move into it whe=\r\nn it is COMPLETE. Alternately, if one occasionally goes and stays in the pa=\r\nlace still under construction (analogy for out of body experiences due to K=\r\nundalini rise), is it an achievement? In fact, it comes with risks. The for=\r\nmer approach is safer and one loses nothing in it. Similarly, one can progr=\r\ness towards complete Self-realization without any out of body experiences. =\r\nThese are not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words to Lord Rama.&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Secondly, one does not get something without wanting it and putti=\r\nng sufficient effort towards it. One may have deeply desired a Kundalini ri=\r\nse in a previous life and may have put enough effort. As a result, one may =\r\nbe getting it now. But one may be unprepared (and ironically may not even w=\r\nant it!) when it comes in this life.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;As you\n do sadhana, try n=\r\not to fancy too many specific&gt; desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in gra=\r\nnting your desires (because of constraints on what Nature can give you righ=\r\nt now, arising from YOUR&gt; OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives =\r\nyou what you want LATE, when you no longer want it or want something else. =\r\nFor example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as =\r\na rich but very sick man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pr=\r\nay whole life for health. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, =\r\nbut not have any knowledge or money. In another &gt; case, one may deeply desi=\r\nre to act in a famous film. One may be reborn &gt; as a tiger or a dog and act=\r\n in a famous film, but not really enjoy that &gt; experience. Basically, peopl=\r\ne keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; something t=\r\nhey are &quot;missing&quot;.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalini, if one de=\r\neply desires an out of body experience given by a\n rising Kundalini and one=\r\n&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it in THIS life, one may be bo=\r\nrn in next life with this specific desire destined to fructify (if there is=\r\n enough karmik force behind it).&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0&gt; *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful, if one is well-prepare=\r\nd in terms of attitude and detachment.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk g=\r\nlued to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it panicked so badly and starte=\r\nd to shake violently. I went to save it from a certain slow death and it wa=\r\ns scared that I would kill it!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glue=\r\nd to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex and scared of being rescu=\r\ned from a certain slow death!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;If our ideas about who we are (v=\r\niz this current body-mind complex) are incorrect and if we are this &quot;infini=\r\nte Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete realization of that at some stag=\r\ne involve stepping out of this body-mind\n complex, without being scared?&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after most undesirab=\r\nle conditioning is overcome, is far better than&gt; Kundalini rise forced when=\r\n some really undesirable conditioning is still left in one&#39;s system.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends one problematic notion about who one is and what=\r\n one needs, another notion that lay buried deeper in consciousness may spri=\r\nng to the surface and torment one. If one overcomes the notion &quot;I am the bo=\r\ndy&quot;, there may be another notion in one&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awar=\r\neness clings on to (e.g. a great doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a=\r\n great saint etc). As an extreme example, if one person had a hidden deep d=\r\nesire to be a great soul who rescues the world, he may fancy that he is a r=\r\ne-incarnated X or Y who will rescue the world now. When one&#39;s self-awarenes=\r\ns (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any such notion, it can cause havoc. T=\r\nhe person may show some\n signs of progress and yet remain in ignorance and =\r\nget stuck badly.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;An awakened Kundalini in a system with undesi=\r\nrable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s weaknesses and wrong notions heavil=\r\ny and cause serious psychiatric and spiritual problems.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;The best approach I recommend is to NOT think in t=\r\nerms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, overcome your&gt; weaknesses =\r\nand improve your detachment over time. Again, I want to emphasize that deta=\r\nchment is not disgust or distaste for life/things/people around you. Disgus=\r\nt is the other side of coin of attachment. It is a negative attachment.&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about &gt; whether your Kundalini rises or not. Worr=\r\ny about whether you are able to resist 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8=\r\n bondages (ashta pashas) or &gt; not. If your ability to resist them is increa=\r\nsing, you are making progress. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you a=\r\nre still making\n progress. When you completely overcome them, Kundalini (yo=\r\nur self-awareness) &gt; will automatically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord=\r\n (true Self).&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;One word on surrende=\r\nring to a personal deity. Though true surrender is helpful, most people do =\r\nnot have it. They simply do business with god. Though people may be offende=\r\nd by my words, this is the plain and bare fact.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;&quot;I want X, I w=\r\nill pray to you and please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini rise, =\r\nI will pray to you and please protect me&quot; - all this is just a business dea=\r\nl. There is something you want and you ask god for it. True surrender has n=\r\no place for agendas, desires, demands or expectations. True surrender is lo=\r\nsing oneself in one&#39;s fascination for the qualities of Lord. True surrender=\r\n is accepting anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or =\r\nhighly painful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it gratefully. True surrende=\r\nr\n is thinking of Lord with fascination and pleasure, even in the face of (=\r\nand during) Death.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;If one without true surrender and with many=\r\n desires and wrong notions experiences a Kundalini rise, one may still be t=\r\nrapped, despite thinking of a personal god. It is not that god does not wan=\r\nt to &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It is not about protecting or endangering=\r\n. If you go back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was =\r\ntrying to protect it, but it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning make=\r\ns one *run away* from God&#39;s&gt; protection! God&#39;s protection may seem to a con=\r\nditioned mind like grave danger that one should run away from!&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether through the path of wisdom or surren=\r\nder, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize that all this is temporary =\r\nand can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while you have and keep doing your =\r\nbest, but be prepared to lose everything anytime. Only detachment\n and a ve=\r\nry light mental conditioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can protect=\r\n one as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and imp=\r\nurities in one&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) and =\r\nstop Her from meeting True Self.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;The real key is how light you=\r\nr conditioning is.&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;Best regards,&gt; &gt;&gt;Narasimha&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&gt; &gt;&gt;A=\r\nstrology & Spirituality Resources: http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&gt; &gt;&gt;-----=\r\n---&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;________________________________&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; From: L=\r\neela Sastry &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; mailto:vedic-w=\r\nisdom%40yahoogroups.com&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;Sent: Thursday, February 28, 2013 6:05 AM&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Kundalini syndrome&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0YES=C2=A0 SIR=C2=A0 , perfectly correct=C2=A0=C2=A0 ,=C2=A0but intens=\r\ne bhakthi and saranagathi=C2=A0 makes the ishtadevatha to stand by the sadh=\r\naka and remove most of the hurdles .=C2=A0=C2=A0All the so called dhyanamar=\r\ngas with out any personal deity and\n manthra allow the other entities to en=\r\nter in to the inner planes who play havoc with the=C2=A0 psyche .=C2=A0 Onc=\r\ne we are under the protection of=C2=A0 a mahadevatha ,all the other=C2=A0 d=\r\nisturbances will definitely=C2=A0 be wiped off . But=C2=A0 it can be attain=\r\ned by the righteous behaviour along with manthranushtana . You have explain=\r\ned very nicely .=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 regards ls .=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;From: rajarshi nandy &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;mailto:vedic-wisdo=\r\nm%40yahoogroups.co