ly these patients ar=\r\ne not well-understood by western medicine, and as we have no treatments for=\r\n deranged&gt; kundalini, we struggle to help them. Many yogis try to forcibly =\r\nwaken the kundalini. My experience with this lady confirmed my feeling that=\r\n kundalini should not be forcibly wakened. This woman wants to kill herself=\r\n at times because the suffering from the deranged energy is so bad. She fee=\r\nls it will consume her, and it is something she cannot escape from. I wonde=\r\nred what solution there could be to her problem. The logical one was to pra=\r\ny to the Divine Mother, who manifests as the kundalini to relieve the suffe=\r\nring of this woman- and either cure her, or give her the strength to bear t=\r\nhis. May I request that the good samaritans among you pray for her, and for=\r\n others like her (whom we may not know of)- their suffering really is pitia=\r\nble. And let us be careful in our sadhana so as not to end\n up in this situ=\r\nation ourselves. Perhaps this is why the bhakti marga is the safest. It is =\r\nperhaps safest to say &quot;let me be your instrument&quot; and leave the kundalini&gt; =\r\nrising bit to God&#39;s will. Om Dum Durgayai Namaha Aparna &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;Reply via=\r\n web post Reply to sender Reply to group Start a New Topic Messages in this=\r\n topic (5) &gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;Recent Activity: &gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;\n&gt;\r\n--1082104826-1621490346-1362207041=:2889\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;html&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:#000; background-color:#fff; font-family:ti=\r\nmes new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:10pt&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;RIGHT: =\r\nauto&quot;&gt;&lt;SPAN style=3D&quot;RIGHT: auto&quot;&gt;&nbsp;Dear sir ,your explanation is very =\r\nbeautiful. But not all&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; cases fall&nbsp; in&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp; wrong direction . The point of discussion is&nbsp; a