, arising from YOUR&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; OWN previ=\r\nous actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want LATE, when you no=\r\n longer want it or want something else. For example, one may pray for great=\r\n wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very sick man in next li=\r\nfe. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for health. In the li=\r\nfe after that, one may be very healthy, but not have any knowledge or money=\r\n. In another &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; case, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film.=\r\n One may be reborn &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; as a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, =\r\nbut not really enjoy that &lt;WBR&gt;&gt; experience. Basically, people keep goin=\r\ng in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;mi=\r\nssing&quot;.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kun=\r\ndalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience\n given by a rising =\r\nKundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it in THIS li=\r\nfe, one may be born in next life with this specific desire destined to fruc=\r\ntify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;W=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &g=\r\nt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful, if one is well-pr=\r\nepared in terms of attitude and detachment.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt=\r\n; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it an=\r\nd it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save it fr=\r\nom a certain slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &g=\r\nt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse=\r\n trap called this body-mind complex and scared of being rescued from a cert=\r