t=\r\nion for the qualities of Lord. True surrender is accepting anything Lord th=\r\nrows one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or highly painful) as Lord&#39;s pras=\r\nad and accepting it gratefully. True surrender is thinking of Lord with fas=\r\ncination and pleasure, even in the face of (and during) Death.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;If one without true surrender and with many de=\r\nsires and wrong\n notions experiences a Kundalini rise, one may still be tra=\r\npped, despite thinking of a personal god. It is not that god does not want =\r\nto &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It is not about protecting or endangering. =\r\nIf you go back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was tr=\r\nying to protect it, but it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning makes =\r\none *run away* from God&#39;s&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; protection! God&#39;s protection may seem to=\r\n a conditioned mind like grave danger that one should run away from!&lt;WBR&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;W=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether through the path of wisdom or surrender, develop di=\r\nspassion and detachment. Realize that all this is temporary and can be take=\r\nn away anytime. Enjoy it while you have and keep doing your best, but be pr=\r\nepared to lose everything anytime. Only detachment and a very light mental\n=\r\n conditioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can protect one as one&#39;s K=\r\nundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and impurities in one&#39;=\r\ns nadis will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) and stop Her from m=\r\neeting True Self.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;The real key is =\r\nhow light your conditioning is.&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Be=\r\nst regards,&lt;WBR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Nar